                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1234a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-20T11:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>53. In view of possible misunderstandings you should not request an American
                    warship to visit any port in Turkey until you have obtained consent of the
                    Ottoman Government to the intended visit and local authorities at the port have
                    been advised by their government.</p>
                <p>Grave apprehension prevails here as to the safety of <persName corresp="#p_CX1"
                        >Christian</persName> missionaries. Represent to the Ottoman Government the
                    seriousness of the situation and urge in most solemn way upon them the necessity
                    of preventing any loss of life or property of missionaries, stating the effect a
                    failure to protect them would have upon the opinion and action of the United
                    States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
